The Quick Reference is a compact summary of the tactics, rules,
conversions, and support functions used most often in day-to-day HOL4
proof.

* The single source is quickref.md.  It feeds both outputs:
  - the mdbook page (part of the unified manual site): `Holmake mdbook`
  - the PDF reference sheet: `Holmake quick.pdf` (needs pandoc + a
    LaTeX installation).

* Entries are written as \refentry{Module.entry}; these become links
  to the corresponding Reference manual page (relative links in the
  mdbook build, links to the online Reference manual in the PDF).
  Names with no separate Reference entry are written as plain code
  spans instead.

* This manual is wired into the unified mdbook site via the MANUALS
  list in Manual/mdbook.mk and the navigation in Manual/theme/index.hbs.
